## Layers on the Canvas

A single page can contain multiple synchronized reasoning layers:

|Layer     |Contents                                   |Live Updates                 |
|----------|-------------------------------------------|-----------------------------|
|Math      |Equations, derivations, proofs             |Yes — algebra engine         |
|Diagram   |Sketches, geometric figures, force diagrams|Yes — geometry engine        |
|Language  |Notes, explanations, problem statements    |Yes — NLP engine             |
|Data      |Tables, measurements, imported datasets    |Yes — data engine            |
|Code      |Runnable snippets, simulations             |Yes — execution engine       |
|Simulation|Animated interactive models                |Yes — physics/dynamics engine|

All layers share the same underlying graph. Writing an equation on the math layer can **automatically generate** a corresponding graph on the simulation layer.

**Example:**

```
User writes: dx/dt = kx
↓
Graph of exponential growth appears
↓
Animated model runs
↓
Parameter sliders appear: adjust k, initial condition
↓
Margin note: "This structure also appears in compound interest, radioactive decay, population growth"
```

