## Specialized AI Assistants

Instead of one general AI, the canvas deploys **specialized reasoning daemons** — each expert in a domain, all sharing the same page graph.

|Assistant |Role                                                       |
|----------|-----------------------------------------------------------|
|Algebra   |Simplifies, checks steps, suggests transformations         |
|Geometry  |Interprets sketches, computes measurements, animates proofs|
|Physics   |Checks units, simulates systems, animates forces           |
|Statistics|Detects patterns in data, generates distributions          |
|Code      |Runs simulations, debugs, suggests implementations         |
|Writing   |Explains reasoning in natural language, detects ambiguity  |
|Analogy   |Detects structural similarity across domains               |
|Critic    |Finds missing steps, invalid inferences, unsupported claims|

They do not operate in isolation. They **collaborate through the shared graph**. The Geometry assistant’s output becomes an input to the Algebra assistant. The Physics assistant flags unit errors that the Writing assistant then explains in the margin.

This is the Pantheon daemon stack instantiated as a reasoning workspace.

