## The Problem Translation Engine

One of the most powerful features: converting **messy real-world descriptions** into **structured mathematical form** on the same page.

User writes:

> “Water tank filling from two pipes. One fills it in 3 hours, the other in 5 hours. How long together?”

AI extracts structure onto the page:

```
Rate₁ = 1/3 tank/hr
Rate₂ = 1/5 tank/hr
Combined rate = Rate₁ + Rate₂ = 8/15 tank/hr
Time = 1 / (8/15) = 15/8 hr ≈ 1.875 hr
```

Then animates: two fill curves rising, combining, reaching full tank.

The canvas is a **reality-to-model translation engine**. The user does not need to know how to formalize — they just describe, and the system finds the structure.

