## Cross-Domain Analogy Detection

The deepest feature. The system recognizes when two problems on different pages — or from different fields — share the same relational structure.

**Example:**

```
Heat diffusion equation: ∂T/∂t = α∇²T
Population spread: ∂P/∂t = D∇²P
Option pricing (Black-Scholes): ∂V/∂t = ½σ²S²∂²V/∂S²
```

These are structurally isomorphic under a field mapping. The system detects this and offers:

> *“This equation has the same structure as heat diffusion and population dynamics. Solutions from those domains may transfer here.”*

This is the `~` operator from the Relation Algebra made operational. Not just finding similar problems — finding **same-shape problems across different symbolic surfaces**.

This is how genuine insight propagates across fields. The canvas makes it visible and actionable.

