## The Personal Cognitive Engine

Over time the canvas builds a model of **how the user thinks**:

|Profile Dimension   |What it tracks                                    |
|--------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
|Strategy preferences|Top-down vs. bottom-up, visual vs. algebraic      |
|Strength map        |Topics and transformation types that come easily  |
|Gap map             |Patterns that consistently fail or get skipped    |
|Analogy fingerprint |Which cross-domain mappings resonate for this user|
|Pace profile        |How long steps take, where hesitation occurs      |
|Creative signatures |Unusual approaches that worked                    |

The workspace becomes a **cognitive prosthetic** — not just a tool that does things for you, but a system that knows how you think and amplifies it.

This is the Kintsugi architecture applied to learning: the fracture patterns (mistakes, hesitations, gaps) are preserved and gilded, not erased.

