## The Symbolic Interface to Reality

The final form of this system is not a tool. It is an **interface**.

You write a model of the world on the canvas.

The system:

- simulates it
- checks it
- explains it
- animates it
- connects it to other models
- shows you what it structurally resembles
- helps you find what you’re missing

Thinking becomes something you can **watch unfold** on the page.

Not a document. Not a file. A **living model of reasoning** — structured, replayable, compressible, shareable, and permanently connected to everything else you have ever thought.

